Kernel modules are expected to use internal kernel APIs directly rather than shelling out to standard Linux commands.

What is the best (and proper) way to execute this?
If you want this code to be upstream-compatible (or just structurally sound), you must do the memory reclamation entirely within kernel space using Memory Management (MM) APIs.
