The Proper Architecture (The Shrinker API):
Rather than forcefully dropping caches on demand, the upstream-approved way to manage memory pressure is to register a Shrinker.

You define a struct shrinker.
You implement a count_objects and scan_objects function.
You register it using register_shrinker().
